Key Match Events: Donyell Malen turned the ball into his own net six minutes into the contest
Cody Gakpo equalised soon after the break
Romano Schmid put Austria ahead again just before the hour in a see-saw second half
Marcel Sabitzer scored the winning goal 10 minutes from time
Post-Match Reflections: Marcel Sabitzer said, 'When you win like that, win the group, score the winning goal, it doesn't get any better than that. You can see that we rotate through the team and nothing is missed, everyone knows their position and what they have to do'
Dutch captain Virgil van Dijk said, 'A very bad match, in all respects. We started weakly in possession and in duels. Then you are behind the times. It was a bad evening.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: Austria's aggressive and hard-running approach propelled them into the round of 16 of the European Championship
The Dutch also advanced as one of the four best third-place finishers despite giving away an early own goal
France held to a 1-1 draw by Poland in the group's other game in Dortmund
Austria topped the table with six points, one ahead of second-placed France on five and the Dutch on four points
